===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|spreden|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|sprædan|sprǣdan|to spread, expand|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|spraidijanan|to spread|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|(s)per-|to strew, sow, sprinkle|lang=en}}. Cognate with West Frisian {{term|spriede||to spread|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|spriedjen||to spread|lang=frr}}, Dutch {{term|spreiden||to spread|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|spreden||to spread|lang=nds}}, German {{term|spreizen||to spread, spread out|lang=de}}, {{etyl|no|-}} {{term|spreida|lang=no}}, {{term|spreie||to spread, disseminate|lang=no}}, Swedish {{term|sprida||to spread|lang=sv}}.

